page.title: 09THE CHURCH,SWAFFHAM BULBECK
page.content: The church is a 13th century church.It is mainly made of clunch,flint and brick.It has a strong oak door with iron on it.The tower has been patched up with new brick.The arch way at the back of the church has got an interesting patern scratched in the clunch.The grave stones are terrebly old.Dead people are now burried in the cemetry.The church is called St.Marys.The church is 750 years old.Bits for the church were added in the 15th century.The pews are also 15th century.The ceiling is made of wood.Inbetween some of the pews the floor is rotton and is falling to bits.In the 17th century stupid people went round knoking the carvings off the end of the pews because they didnt believe in them.So when you go into the church you only see half of the carvings left.
